reviews_data.review_text: I go to this coffee shop almost every Thursday morning. The sweet red headed barista, Tressa, always makes my coffee perfect. I literally gave up on coffee until she started making it for me. She’s always so kind and makes the atmosphere feel welcoming and comfortable. She even learned my mom’s regular order and always has it ready to go before we even have to ask. Such a cute place and amazing customer service.
Amazing barista and good coffee, y'all have to try the Vietnamese coffee
I have been here a couple of times and the drinks are always great. I've been helped by various baristas and every time they make me feel comfortable and happy to be there.

I visited this coffee shop with a couple of friends, and the service was excellent. We were warmly welcomed as soon as we walked in, and the barista was kind and helpful, answering all our questions. The aesthetic of the place was also amazing—super cozy and cute! It’s perfect for a date, taking Instagram-worthy photos, or just hanging out with friends. The coffee was good, though some of the drinks could use a bit more flavor.
Love the coffee drinks and pastries. The owners are wonderful…always so welcoming. Comfortable cafe seating indoors and out.

Love this place, my friend and I were trying to find a coffee shop that I could bring my dog to and we stumbled upon Bill and Bobs. This place has a nice size patio area and water bowl for pups. The employees were so lovely and welcoming. I was able to bring my pup inside for a pup cup and to order and he even got a couple extra treats. Would highly recommend this place! ❤️
Great Aa meeting

This is a little hidden gem and I just love the coffee here. I always come in late morning on the weekends and it can get busy, but the coffee is absolutely worth the wait. If you like good coffee and having a nice little chat with your barista, who also gives great recommendations if you have one of those days where you cannot decide, this is the perfect place for you. They have outdoor seating too and more seating in the back if you like it a bit cooler and quieter.

Had my first Cafe con Leche  here and it was absolutely delicious. The barista on Saturday morning was knowledgeable and friendly. Service was fast. Highly recommend the Cinnamon Crunch muffin as well. Atmosphere was quiet and friendly. We will be back!

I hesitate to write this because I really admire this shop for the fact that they give back to the AA community. My brother had recommended it after going in and meeting the owner. Unfortunately, they were having a rough morning when I went. Out of coffee lids (no big deal, but haven’t seen this before at a coffee shop), girl taking orders was being trained I think by the barista, who was kinda gruff and I could hear her complaining that the owner never let them close even in “a ****ing storm” haha so that was awkward. It was like when someone kinda hates their job and you can feel it. I thought the girl who took my order was a lovely person though, and was clearly overwhelmed. I felt so bad for her. I waited a long time in line and then waited about 10 min for my latte so I went and asked about it and it had been forgotten. Again, I get it. Things happen. The nail in the coffin was the coffee sadly. My latte tasted like bitter drip coffee with burnt foamy milk in it. :/ to be fair, I am a coffee snob. I make my own lattes every morning. I have high standards but I think it’s fair in this economy, and I wish I’d gone to another shop that gives latte art and- sorry but real lattes for the same price. I am glad the money goes to a good cause. Now, again- I think she was being trained so I get learning, but the coffee itself was clearly not of the highest quality. If I used the beans I have at home, I couldn’t make them taste that burnt and bitter, and I’ve pulled bad shots with them. Oh, also- the barista stopped making drinks to go over and talk to a patron about his dog. That’s while I was waiting on my forgotten drink…
I really hated to post this but if you’re a coffee lover who frequents the charlotte area coffee scene, this one’s… not quite on that level. 💗
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry about your experience. Can you tell me what day this was please.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee! I had an oat milk latte with toasted marshmallow and my husband had a pour over. Both fantastic! The place looks small from the outside but the inside has a really cute and cozy place to enjoy your coffee.
A pretty small place but clean and the barista was friendly. I received my drink half empty and the drink itself was bitter and didn't really taste like anything. The price was low, though.
The pictures are very misleading, there was barely any seating inside. The Chai Latte tasted not like chai as well. Do not waste your time here.
Hidden gem. Great coffee.
Great spot for coffee, a pastry and working remotely. Nice spacious room in the back so bring your laptop and get your work done while you enjoy a latte and a muffin.

I'm sorry but how can you serve hot coffee without having a non-toxic stirrer?
I asked for a stirrer to mix the sugar in my hot coffee
The lady said all she has to offer me is a plastic straw.
I asked for a metal spoon at least that clearly they do have over there but she refused.

Come on people it's 2025
You are selling an espresso shot and a latte for almost $9

Please get some wood or metal stirrer so we don't have to poison ourselves when we mixed the coffee you make
Had a good experience here doing work!

Coffee was great and very clean and a nice atmosphere. I never write reviews but the lady who took my order was honestly pretty rude, judged my friend for what she ordered and then rudely corrected me on what i should order. just didn’t like the way she spoke to us, she was a older lady with glasses.
Always amazing customer service and a great cup of coffee! Very cool atmosphere if needing a quiet place to work or study. Plenty of outlets and tables available.

This is a really great coffee shop.  From the outside it just looks like a normal shop, but inside it’s so much more.   It was empty when we visited yesterday.  There was a gentlemen who was at the counter.  As soon as he started talking I just knew he was from NY.   I explained I was from there as well and we just started chatting.  We placed our order and then the gentleman (Albert) the owner was preparing our order and gave us the story.

He bought the coffee shop 2 years ago and it’s a AA/Al-Anon meeting place at night.  He said they get so many people and the whole back room is dedicated to the cause.  The coffee shop puts the money back into shop to keep it running for the meetings.  I could have talked to him all day about it as it was quite interesting.  He also said he hires people from the meetings to help run the coffee shop!

Anyways, if you want to be a part of this wonderful cause, visit this shop.  The coffee was amazing and we shared a piece of carrot cake which was delish.  Pricing was fair for a coffee shop!

Thanks Albert for  being kind to us today and telling your story!
I had the Iced Cafe con leche which was fantastic. Sat outside and once I finished, I had to get another.
The service was spectacular! The coffee was amazing!
Friendly service. Cozy atmosphere . Delicious coffee.
Great coffee and great cookies. Puts the chains to shame!
I got a white chocolate latte, and let me tell you, it was tasty! Barista was friendly, and I knew from the first sip, I would be a repeat customer.  Cute little spot with fantastic coffee.
The best coffee ever!
Pleasantly surprised to find this coffee bar.  Very reasonably priced custom coffee drinks and a comfy place to enjoy them.  Excellent.  My new coffee place😍
LOVE this spot! Great vibe & great coffee. So happy we have this place near home!

I had the pleasure of ordering a quad shot vanilla latte at Bill and Bob's Coffee Bar, and I have to say, it was absolutely worth it! The barista with blonde hair and purple streaks did a really good job. The espresso shots were rich and the vanilla perfectly balanced. I'll definitely be coming back for more!
Amazing chai and matcha latte!!! Yummy baklava and pecan pie, great vibe and service, love it !!!

I am picky about my coffee and I didn't have high expectations for Stallings, but this was awful.
Visited on a Sunday afternoon and the staff was friendly. Coffee was awful - if they even put any in my iced coffee. I asked for an iced coffee with a little splash of creamer. I had a watered down creamer drink. As I was waiting on my drink to be made the staff was explaining the process of pulling an espresso shot to another customer and it was clear the staff did not know much about pulling a shot. She then proceeded to allow the customer to touch the tamper and then used it to pull another customers shot - GROSS.
The food is all purchased from a store and resold - a missed opportunity to partner with a local baker.
It was dark in the back room - no lightbulbs in any of the hanging lamps.
The staff had brought their dog (also ew) who was roaming around and child who was trying his best to be quiet - but he's a kid who was extremely bored. Not the atmosphere to study in or friendly to those who are allergic to animals.
Took one sip and had to leave a review. Its really good. You should never go to starbucks with places like this around.
The owner is a very nice person. Atmosphere is cozy. Though, I wish they had fruity beans for espresso. Still it is fresh.

Beautiful charming place. Clean and inviting. The owner is awesome.
Highly recommended

Great service! Great Atmosphere! Great Conversation! Amazing cafe con leche! I felt like I was back home in Tampa! Pleasantly surprised we stopped in on the way back to Fayetteville from our daughters' cross country race for a pick me up. So glad we did! We will be back next time we are in the Matthews area!
Girl behind the counter couldn't get through my order without hitting her vape. My drink tasted like dirty water. And she almost forgot to cash me out. Hard pass.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Sorry for your experience she is no longer with us. I’m the owner and would love to make you an amazing cup of coffee on me.

reviews_data.review_text: Very poor customer service

I visited Bill & Bob’s today and had a great experience. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, perfect for catching up with friends or getting some work done. The staff is incredibly friendly and knowledgeable, always ready to recommend a great brew or help with any special requests.

The coffee itself is top-notch—rich, flavorful, and clearly made with care. I tried the breve and was blown away by the quality. Just to say the least, extremely picky and this was amazing!

Whether you're a coffee connoisseur or just looking for a comfortable spot to relax, Bill & Bob’s is a MUST visit. I’ll definitely be back!
The environment feels so safe to be able to open up and have meeting here. It’s also such a great vibe to just hang out and have a coffee or work on the computer. Im so grateful I found this place!
So cute, super nice barista and the iced latte was delicious!!
Coffee tastes amazing and the price is excellent. The barista was so kind and seemed eager to answer any questions. Definitely put this cafe on your list to try!
Friendly service! Great coffee!
Very nice and cozy place, hidden gem
Really cool atmosphere, fantastic prices and excellent coffee. Great pastey offering as well. Was not aware that this was here, will definitely be back!
Great customer service,  plenty of seating, great atmosphere to enjoy conversation, and a cup of coffee!
Awesome place! Owner is great and comfortable seating. Made a coffee up on a whim and owner might add to menu banana mocha! Definitely worth stopping in

This coffee shop was an unexpected pleasure. The coffee was delicious, but the atmosphere was what was such a pleasant surprise. It has plenty of comfortable seating and a chill vibe. The owner, Albert, was welcoming and friendly. I will visit this little gem again!

One of my favorite coffee shops around the Charlotte area. Great tasting coffee and snacks. Awesome people that walk in and amazing service. Cool atmosphere to hang out, have a meeting, or get work done. Always stopping by when I am in the area

I went in to Bill and Bob’s just on a whim. I went in for a quick cup of coffee and my plan was to grab it and hit the road. Little did I know that I would end up enjoying a two hour conversation with Al and his amazing daughter that just so happened to be in town for a couple of days. This experience turned into an amazing fulfillment of my soul and not just an average cup of Joe. If you are looking for quite possibly the best quality cup of coffee, no matter what way you like it served. This is the place for you hands-down if you want that coffee shop that allows you to come in grab a cup and sit down and enjoy this is the place for you thank you Al for quite possibly the best coffee bar experience that I’ve ever received. if I ever return to Monroe North Carolina, I will be back!

Beautiful place. Has plenty of space to do either your work or just read a book or chat with your friends.  Coffee was delicious as well. Had a great time catching up with my old friend. I would highly recommend it.

Stopped by this little coffee shop and found out why so many people like it.  The barista, Al, was incredible and made our experience top notch.  The local owned shop definitely focuses on the surrounding community and gives back in many ways.  The coffee was excellent and they can pretty much make it any way you want!  We also love the fact they support other local businesses by only using local fresh roasted beans.  If you are ever near Stallings you need to stop by for a cup!
Al is great! God bless you bro

This was my first time coming to this unique little shop. I was absolutely blown away with the welcoming feeling and unique cause they represent. This cause hit home for myself and the friend that came with me. I would highly recommend to anyone.
What a novel little coffee bar. Nestled in the corner of a strip mall. Supporting people making  a change in there life. I'm all about people supporting people. Much love for this place!!!
So happy I found this place. It is quaint and cozy. My Vietamese coffee was the best I ever had.
Awesome, super chill
I had such an enjoyable experience, wonderful and lively owners. They were kind enough to remake my drink to get it just right! Had a delicious latte and will be back!
Great afajores, amazing coffee, even better company. Highly recommend.  I needed to get away and 😌.  Perfect place to do just that.
Had a delicious cup of Cuban coffee.. great little spot and I just found out there's a 7:30 Wednesday night AA meeting there.. definitely be back... a place I can call home..

Beyond Sober hosted an event at Bill and Bobs Coffee Bar tonight. They had live music, food, games, and great fellowship. I got to buy a namaste sober shirt, a medallion for a friend, and a handmade bracelet of red lava rock with leo ♌️ symbol.

This coffee shop is bringing much needed sober events to our community.

Thank you!

Nice coffee joint.  Friendly person behind the bar but slow service.  I did have something that took time to brew and the Colada was perfection.  The chairs at the bar were wobbly as heck.  The pastry was okay.  This is not DD or Tarbucks.
Very friendly and helpful staff. We will be back soon!
Very cool experience. Love the origins of this coffee bar and the coffee was delicious as well!

Went for the 1st time today just to check it out. Did a little research on the history of the Bill and Bob's Coffee Bar. Awesome. Got some iced Chai. It was good. Did not plan on staying, but stayed about a hour. Have a great time talking with Juliet. Will definitely be back.
First time having Turkish coffee and it was amazing. Super nice host/barista kept casual conversation and the atmosphere is very relaxing. Definitely coming back whenever I'm in the area!

When there on a whim since we were in the area. Coffee was some of the best I’ve had. Chatted with the barista who was very down to earth, super helpful and nice. Amazing place. Wish we lived closer so we could go more often. Five stars is too low.

Amazing new coffee house smack between Matthews & Indian Trail. Indoor and outdoor seating. Outlets everywhere. International coffee too. The Turkish coffee and Cuban Colada are out of this world. Laid back vibe. Love 💗💗 it.
Great place! Will definitely be going back!
Best chai latte in at least 789 mile radius!!!
Just discovered this shop. Amazing coffee and experience. Great service and conversation with Albert. Highly recommend this local gem.
Great coffee and great company.
Amazing experience. Super friendly and all around a nice place to grab coffee and chat.

Great christian coffee shop, they have some food items but mostly drinks. They have a rewards system also, and very cute inside and outside seating. Really gives me vibes of the coffee shops in Alaska, I'd recommend checking it out.

This is the best coffee shop I have been to in the Matthews and Charlotte area. They have a super chill vibe and offer lots of coffee options from drip to Turkish coffee. You can tell the beans are fresh!

I love this place! Amazing for the community💕 Thank you!!!
Great selection of coffee and pastries. I am excited to come back with my friends🤩

Bill and Bob's Coffee Bar is the place to go if you want an excellent cup of coffee, a masterfully pulled shot of espresso or a specialty drink like a Cuban Colada or Turkish coffee prepared the authentic way. The atmosphere within the coffee shop is welcoming and relaxing. They purchase coffee from local roasters (currently Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters and Magnolia Coffee Company) to ensure that the coffee is as fresh as possible. I was there for over 2 hours and had 4 drinks. The Cuban Colada was perfectly sweet and strong, the shot of espresso had an excellent flavor and was NOT BITTER AT ALL, the regular drip coffee was smooth and hot, and the cold brew was smooth and refreshing. Al has got to be one of the most interesting people that I have met in a long time, and he is super knowledgeable and passionate when it comes to the coffee he serves. If you're not quite sure what to get, ask Al and he will point you in the right direction. Everyone wants to support a small business with a real mission and Bill and Bob's have one worth getting behind. I will be visiting this coffee shop frequently.

P.S. If you want to get the best experience, remind Al to cut off the fluorescent lights...it's a whole vibe!
Got a great Cuban coffee !!!
Love my girl Juliette! She made my coffee perfectly. So friendly! And ice cream for my kiddo was a nice option also.

Great place to stop by for coffee! Had a meeting here and it’s so small and cozy inside that it’s really got a homey vibe. Tried the Turkish coffee pictured and it was epic! Presentation was on point and the service was kind and courteous. Just kind of found this spot out of the blue but definitely want to stop by for more!
Wonderful place to bring my dog after she has treatment at the vet. Always gets a generous pup cup and the staff is so kind and personable.
Not your Momma’s coffee bar. Laid back lounge atmosphere. Lovely service. Smooth energy.
Great place! Excellent coffee! Nice people!
Awesome little coffee shop, with the best coffee. Very cool atmosphere with a great background story

Stumbled across this place from a google search and fell in love with this coffee shop the moment I walked in! The aroma and atmosphere is captivating, Once I tasted my dessert latte I knew Bill and Bobs would become a daily stop on my commute! Looking forwards to trying all the different styles of coffee in the menu 😊
Great place, great aromas, and very friendly staff. The Turkish coffee was great.
Cozy spot, barista was very friendly and clearly enjoys his job. Iced caramel latte was solid. Go for conversation and good coffee!
Awesome spot, owner does an amazing job and is an amazing person. Highly recommended!
This is an absolute must go to place! Clean and quant environment with a beautiful meaning to its start! Will definitely be back as a regular
Excellent customer service. Coffee, pastry great!!

Perfect place to work from 'home', plenty of outlets, and great wifi. The coffee is chefs kiss, you can really tell it's great quality. So happy a place like this opened up, will definitely become a regular!

This coffee shop is great
Great people and coffee is out of this world …you want some god coffee or a place just to sit and relax
This is the spot to go
You won’t be disappointed.

Amazing coffee, great atmosphere, with warm & welcoming hospitality! Good place to just chill, or even study/work & chill! So if you're ever in the Matthews NC area...make sure to add, visit Bill & Bob's Coffee Bar to your itinerary
Great coffee, lots of options on drinks! Flat whites and mocha lattes are great
Great environment, as my family and I love the non traditional layout and amazing coffee!!!
The Best coffee I’ve had in years!!!! The customer service was above the standard of what I was used to. Definitely recommend stopping in and trying the Caramel Macchiato.

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: This establishment is wonderful the atmosphere is great and friendly also the staff takes care of you and puts that extra bit of loving care❤️ coffee is A+. do yourself a favor and get down there and enjoy a great cup of ☕ coffee everything is great! You won't regret it I will definitely be visiting every day for my daily cup of coffee! Owner did a fantastic job!

The work put into this coffee bar is amazing! The vibes, the coffee just outstanding. Freshly brewed at that! Finally a local coffee spot i can head to every morning before and after work! Definitely a must if you haven’t been here you wont regret it!
Fantastic, new coffee shop. Al and staff were were very welcoming and true coffee lovers. Great local spot!

I visited Bill & Bob’s today and had a great experience. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, perfect for catching up with friends or getting some work done. The staff is incredibly friendly and knowledgeable, always ready to recommend a great brew or help with any special requests.

The coffee itself is top-notch—rich, flavorful, and clearly made with care. I tried the breve and was blown away by the quality. Just to say the least, extremely picky and this was amazing!

Whether you're a coffee connoisseur or just looking for a comfortable spot to relax, Bill & Bob’s is a MUST visit. I’ll definitely be back!
The environment feels so safe to be able to open up and have meeting here. It’s also such a great vibe to just hang out and have a coffee or work on the computer. Im so grateful I found this place!
So cute, super nice barista and the iced latte was delicious!!
Coffee tastes amazing and the price is excellent. The barista was so kind and seemed eager to answer any questions. Definitely put this cafe on your list to try!
Friendly service! Great coffee!
Very nice and cozy place, hidden gem
Really cool atmosphere, fantastic prices and excellent coffee. Great pastey offering as well. Was not aware that this was here, will definitely be back!
Great customer service,  plenty of seating, great atmosphere to enjoy conversation, and a cup of coffee!
Awesome place! Owner is great and comfortable seating. Made a coffee up on a whim and owner might add to menu banana mocha! Definitely worth stopping in

This coffee shop was an unexpected pleasure. The coffee was delicious, but the atmosphere was what was such a pleasant surprise. It has plenty of comfortable seating and a chill vibe. The owner, Albert, was welcoming and friendly. I will visit this little gem again!

One of my favorite coffee shops around the Charlotte area. Great tasting coffee and snacks. Awesome people that walk in and amazing service. Cool atmosphere to hang out, have a meeting, or get work done. Always stopping by when I am in the area

I went in to Bill and Bob’s just on a whim. I went in for a quick cup of coffee and my plan was to grab it and hit the road. Little did I know that I would end up enjoying a two hour conversation with Al and his amazing daughter that just so happened to be in town for a couple of days. This experience turned into an amazing fulfillment of my soul and not just an average cup of Joe. If you are looking for quite possibly the best quality cup of coffee, no matter what way you like it served. This is the place for you hands-down if you want that coffee shop that allows you to come in grab a cup and sit down and enjoy this is the place for you thank you Al for quite possibly the best coffee bar experience that I’ve ever received. if I ever return to Monroe North Carolina, I will be back!

Beautiful place. Has plenty of space to do either your work or just read a book or chat with your friends.  Coffee was delicious as well. Had a great time catching up with my old friend. I would highly recommend it.

Stopped by this little coffee shop and found out why so many people like it.  The barista, Al, was incredible and made our experience top notch.  The local owned shop definitely focuses on the surrounding community and gives back in many ways.  The coffee was excellent and they can pretty much make it any way you want!  We also love the fact they support other local businesses by only using local fresh roasted beans.  If you are ever near Stallings you need to stop by for a cup!
Al is great! God bless you bro

This was my first time coming to this unique little shop. I was absolutely blown away with the welcoming feeling and unique cause they represent. This cause hit home for myself and the friend that came with me. I would highly recommend to anyone.
What a novel little coffee bar. Nestled in the corner of a strip mall. Supporting people making  a change in there life. I'm all about people supporting people. Much love for this place!!!
So happy I found this place. It is quaint and cozy. My Vietamese coffee was the best I ever had.
Awesome, super chill
I had such an enjoyable experience, wonderful and lively owners. They were kind enough to remake my drink to get it just right! Had a delicious latte and will be back!
Great afajores, amazing coffee, even better company. Highly recommend.  I needed to get away and 😌.  Perfect place to do just that.
Had a delicious cup of Cuban coffee.. great little spot and I just found out there's a 7:30 Wednesday night AA meeting there.. definitely be back... a place I can call home..

Beyond Sober hosted an event at Bill and Bobs Coffee Bar tonight. They had live music, food, games, and great fellowship. I got to buy a namaste sober shirt, a medallion for a friend, and a handmade bracelet of red lava rock with leo ♌️ symbol.

This coffee shop is bringing much needed sober events to our community.

Thank you!

Nice coffee joint.  Friendly person behind the bar but slow service.  I did have something that took time to brew and the Colada was perfection.  The chairs at the bar were wobbly as heck.  The pastry was okay.  This is not DD or Tarbucks.
Very friendly and helpful staff. We will be back soon!
Very cool experience. Love the origins of this coffee bar and the coffee was delicious as well!

Went for the 1st time today just to check it out. Did a little research on the history of the Bill and Bob's Coffee Bar. Awesome. Got some iced Chai. It was good. Did not plan on staying, but stayed about a hour. Have a great time talking with Juliet. Will definitely be back.
First time having Turkish coffee and it was amazing. Super nice host/barista kept casual conversation and the atmosphere is very relaxing. Definitely coming back whenever I'm in the area!

When there on a whim since we were in the area. Coffee was some of the best I’ve had. Chatted with the barista who was very down to earth, super helpful and nice. Amazing place. Wish we lived closer so we could go more often. Five stars is too low.

Amazing new coffee house smack between Matthews & Indian Trail. Indoor and outdoor seating. Outlets everywhere. International coffee too. The Turkish coffee and Cuban Colada are out of this world. Laid back vibe. Love 💗💗 it.
Great place! Will definitely be going back!
Best chai latte in at least 789 mile radius!!!
Just discovered this shop. Amazing coffee and experience. Great service and conversation with Albert. Highly recommend this local gem.
Great coffee and great company.
Amazing experience. Super friendly and all around a nice place to grab coffee and chat.

Great christian coffee shop, they have some food items but mostly drinks. They have a rewards system also, and very cute inside and outside seating. Really gives me vibes of the coffee shops in Alaska, I'd recommend checking it out.

This is the best coffee shop I have been to in the Matthews and Charlotte area. They have a super chill vibe and offer lots of coffee options from drip to Turkish coffee. You can tell the beans are fresh!

I love this place! Amazing for the community💕 Thank you!!!
Great selection of coffee and pastries. I am excited to come back with my friends🤩

Bill and Bob's Coffee Bar is the place to go if you want an excellent cup of coffee, a masterfully pulled shot of espresso or a specialty drink like a Cuban Colada or Turkish coffee prepared the authentic way. The atmosphere within the coffee shop is welcoming and relaxing. They purchase coffee from local roasters (currently Sugar Creek Coffee Roasters and Magnolia Coffee Company) to ensure that the coffee is as fresh as possible. I was there for over 2 hours and had 4 drinks. The Cuban Colada was perfectly sweet and strong, the shot of espresso had an excellent flavor and was NOT BITTER AT ALL, the regular drip coffee was smooth and hot, and the cold brew was smooth and refreshing. Al has got to be one of the most interesting people that I have met in a long time, and he is super knowledgeable and passionate when it comes to the coffee he serves. If you're not quite sure what to get, ask Al and he will point you in the right direction. Everyone wants to support a small business with a real mission and Bill and Bob's have one worth getting behind. I will be visiting this coffee shop frequently.

P.S. If you want to get the best experience, remind Al to cut off the fluorescent lights...it's a whole vibe!
Got a great Cuban coffee !!!
Love my girl Juliette! She made my coffee perfectly. So friendly! And ice cream for my kiddo was a nice option also.

Great place to stop by for coffee! Had a meeting here and it’s so small and cozy inside that it’s really got a homey vibe. Tried the Turkish coffee pictured and it was epic! Presentation was on point and the service was kind and courteous. Just kind of found this spot out of the blue but definitely want to stop by for more!
Wonderful place to bring my dog after she has treatment at the vet. Always gets a generous pup cup and the staff is so kind and personable.
Not your Momma’s coffee bar. Laid back lounge atmosphere. Lovely service. Smooth energy.
Great place! Excellent coffee! Nice people!
Awesome little coffee shop, with the best coffee. Very cool atmosphere with a great background story

Stumbled across this place from a google search and fell in love with this coffee shop the moment I walked in! The aroma and atmosphere is captivating, Once I tasted my dessert latte I knew Bill and Bobs would become a daily stop on my commute! Looking forwards to trying all the different styles of coffee in the menu 😊
Great place, great aromas, and very friendly staff. The Turkish coffee was great.
Cozy spot, barista was very friendly and clearly enjoys his job. Iced caramel latte was solid. Go for conversation and good coffee!
Awesome spot, owner does an amazing job and is an amazing person. Highly recommended!
This is an absolute must go to place! Clean and quant environment with a beautiful meaning to its start! Will definitely be back as a regular
Excellent customer service. Coffee, pastry great!!

Perfect place to work from 'home', plenty of outlets, and great wifi. The coffee is chefs kiss, you can really tell it's great quality. So happy a place like this opened up, will definitely become a regular!

This coffee shop is great
Great people and coffee is out of this world …you want some god coffee or a place just to sit and relax
This is the spot to go
You won’t be disappointed.

Amazing coffee, great atmosphere, with warm & welcoming hospitality! Good place to just chill, or even study/work & chill! So if you're ever in the Matthews NC area...make sure to add, visit Bill & Bob's Coffee Bar to your itinerary
Great coffee, lots of options on drinks! Flat whites and mocha lattes are great
Great environment, as my family and I love the non traditional layout and amazing coffee!!!
The Best coffee I’ve had in years!!!! The customer service was above the standard of what I was used to. Definitely recommend stopping in and trying the Caramel Macchiato.
